      <!-- ================================================ -->
      <!-- WHAT THIS IS                                     -->
      <!-- ================================================ -->
      <section id="what" class="intro">
        <div class="container-default">
          <div class="intro-eyebrow">
            <div class="rule" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="rule-glyph metallic">✦</span>
            </div>
            <div class="eyebrow metallic">what this is</div>
          </div>
          <h2>
            A persistent Elder Scrolls V roleplay server, built on SkyMP and
            kept wholly open source.
          </h2>

          <div class="intro-prose">
            <p>
              Frostfall is a narrative multiplayer server for Skyrim Special
              Edition, running on the
              <a href="https://github.com/skyrim-multiplayer/skymp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SkyMP</a>
              framework. Every system we write (economy, politics, justice,
              crafting) ships publicly on
              <a
                href="https://github.com/F02K/Frostfall-Server"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                >GitHub</a
              >
              as we build it. The code is open, the commits are live, and
              anyone who wants to see how a world runs can read it directly.
            </p>
            <p>
              It is built for the players <strong>Bethesda left behind</strong>:
              the ones who remember when worldbuilding had weight, when factions
              had consequence, when the world felt tactile. The main quest, the
              Dragonborn, the prophecy all belong to a different decade.
              <em
                >Player stories fill that space, and the staff seed the world
                rather than run it.</em
              >
            </p>
            <p>
              We are standing up a living Skyrim, in the decade before the one
              you know, and giving it back to the people who fell in love with
              Tamriel the first time. The mods we lean on, the servers we fork,
              the systems we invent all ship freely, because that is how this
              province was built to begin with.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

