        <div class="container">
          <div class="vision-eyebrow">
            <div class="rule" aria-hidden="true">
              <span class="rule-glyph metallic">✦</span>
            </div>
            <div class="eyebrow metallic">our vision</div>
          </div>
          <h2>
            A world <em>players</em> run, and a codebase anyone can inherit.
          </h2>

          <div class="vision-grid">
            <article class="vision-pillar">
              <h3>Staff seed. Players govern.</h3>
              <p>
                Every Jarl, every Steward, every faction head is a vetted
                player. Staff plant the first Jarls and the first leaders of
                the Legion, the Thalmor, the College. Everything beneath that
                propagates through fiction. Enforcement happens in-character
                first: the Thalmor curbs the College, a Jarl corrects their
                guard, a rival merchant undercuts a price. In-world power
                takes precedence over out-of-character moderation wherever
                possible.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="vision-pillar">
              <h3>Real stakes, real theatre.</h3>
              <p>
                The world keeps score. A Downed character is incapacitated and
                can recover. Captivity has a twenty-four-hour ceiling.
                Bounties are per-hold and persistent. A Jarl's record on you
                is a record you carry. The systems exist to texture story, and
                the consequences of your choices outlive the session you made
                them in.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="vision-pillar">
              <h3>Open source, in public.</h3>
              <p>
                The gamemode is written in TypeScript on the
                <a
                  href="https://github.com/F02K/Frostfall-Server"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  >Frostfall-Server</a
                >
                fork of SkyMP, and every commit lands on GitHub as we make it.
                Fifteen systems, 415 passing tests, plan documents and
                changelogs written in the open. If you want to contribute, or
                stand up your own server on top of ours, the door is open.
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

