                <span class="rule-glyph metallic">✦</span>
              </div>
              <div class="eyebrow metallic">gold, power, and consequence</div>
            </div>
            <h2>Every hold has leverage.<br />Every transaction has politics.</h2>

            <div class="economy-grid">
              <article class="economy-card">
                <h3>Nine treasuries. Nine economies.</h3>
                <p>
                  Each hold controls an independent treasury that funds guards,
                  clears bounties, and bankrolls faction activity. A Jarl who
                  lets their coffers run dry has already begun to lose.
                </p>
              </article>
              <article class="economy-card">
                <h3>Trade routes are power.</h3>
                <p>
                  Whiterun's plains feed the province. The Reach yields silver.
                  Haafingar commands the ports. Control the roads between them,
                  and you might get rich. Or, you might get arrested; either's possible.
                </p>
              </article>
              <article class="economy-card">
                <h3>Skills and experience.</h3>
                <p>
                  The more you do, the better you get. Study at the College,
                  train under a master, work a forge. Skills are capped by your
                  faction rank and raised by putting in the hours. Nobody starts
                  an expert, and nobody stays a novice who actually shows up.
                </p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>

